.TH HYPRCURSOR\-UTIL 1 "2025-12-14" "hyprcursor 0.1.13" "Hyprland Ecosystem"
.SH NAME
hyprcursor\-util \- compile, extract, and convert hyprcursor and xcursor themes
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hyprcursor\-util
.I operation
.I path
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hyprcursor\-util
is a utility for converting between cursor theme formats.
It works with three cursor theme states:
compiled hyprcursor themes (usable by applications and compositors),
compiled xcursor themes (usable by the xcursor library),
and working state (a navigable format with PNG/SVG cursors and metadata files).
.PP
The hyprcursor format addresses limitations of the XCursor format by offering
automatic scaling with configurable per-cursor methods, SVG (vector) cursor
support, and significantly better space efficiency.
.SH OPERATIONS
An operation must be specified as the first argument.
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-create " " \fIpath\fR
Create a compiled hyprcursor theme from a working state directory.
.TP
.BR \-x ", " \-\-extract " " \fIpath\fR
Extract an xcursor theme into a working state directory.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Display version information.
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-output " " \fIdirectory\fR
Specify the output directory.
The theme will be written to a subdirectory named
.IR ACTION _ NAME
within this directory.
.TP
.BR \-\-resize " " \fImode\fR
Specify a default resize algorithm for shapes (used during extract operations).
The default is none.
.SH DEPENDENCIES
The
.B xcur2png
utility is required at runtime for extracting xcursor themes.
.SH FILES
Cursor themes are typically stored in
.I ~/.local/share/icons
or
.IR ~/.icons .
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR Hyprland (1),
.BR hyprctl (1)
